      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">(Copy ¶ ) ¶ St George, Queensland ¶ 10 Sept. 1881. ¶ The Hon. the Chief Secretary of Victoria ¶ Melbourne ¶ ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">M81.09.10</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From John Skuthorpe to Bryan O'Loghlen</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Sammlung Perthes Archiv,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">SPA ARCH<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">PGM<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">328</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>Forschungsbibliothek Gotha der Universität Erfurt.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Skuthorpe's letter was presumably sent to Gotha by M.</p>
               </note>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">(Copy</hi>
               </seg>)</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">St George, Queensland</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">10 Sept. 1881.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The Hon. the Chief Secretary of Victoria</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Melbourne</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir —</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I beg to report to you my return here from the Western Country, and to inform you that I have possession of the following relics of the Leichardt<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e. Leichhaardt.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>-Expedition. Leichardt's and Classan's<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Classen?</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>journals, a telescope and a compass. Will you appoint a competent agent to take delivery of them on the following terms?</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A binding agreement to be entered into between us securing me the payment of £6000 on delivery of the articles named, and protecting me against all claims which may be made against me by any persons interested in the ownership of them. I bind myself to deliver them in St George and to place my services at the disposal of your Government, if required, for the space of six months, without further payment, and to point out all localities connected with the discovery, the grave containing Classan's remains, and give every information and assistance to whoever you think fit to appoint.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Your obedient Servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J. R. Skuthorpe</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A cutting from the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 20 September 1881, p. 6, of a very similar letter from Skuthorpe to the Prime Minister of NSW, Sir Henry Parkes, signed ‘John Richard Skuthorpe’, is filed with the MS.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>See also M to E. Behm, 12 October 1881.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
